Jack received 10 emails in the morning, 5 emails in the afternoon and 4 emails in the evening. How many more emails did Jack receive in the afternoon than in the evening??
A. 1 more
B. 2 more
C. 3 more
D. 4 more
E. 5 more
Jack received 10 emails in the morning, 5 emails in the afternoon and 4 emails in the evening.
So, the total number of emails received by Jack in a day = 10 + 5 + 4 = 19
Now, the number of emails received in the afternoon = 5
So, the number of emails received in the evening = 4
So, the number of more emails received in the afternoon than in the evening = 5 – 4 = 1
So, the correct answer is option (A).

B. 23 bottle caps
C. 25 bottle caps
D. 27 bottle caps
E. 29 bottle caps
A. 21 bottle caps.
Danny collected 30 bottle caps at the park and threw away 63 old ones.
So, he threw away 63 - 30 = 33 bottle caps.
So, he threw away 33 bottle caps more than those he found at the park.
So, he threw away 33 + 30 = 63 bottle caps.
So, he threw away 63 - 30 = 33 bottle caps.
So, he threw away 33 bottle caps more than those he found at the park
